(10015, 'tej', 'eastham', 'works with all types of pets', 'data:image/jpeg;base64,', 5, 'Certified Professional Dog Trainer (CPDT)', 'Dog trainers specialize in teaching dogs obedience, manners, and various commands. They may work with puppies, adult dogs, or even specialize in training service or therapy dogs.', 6),
(10016, 'paaji', 'Waterloo', 'Clicker training and enrichment activities', 'https://www.google.com/imgres?q=linkedin%20profile%20picture&imgurl=https%3A%2F%2Fmarketplace.canva.com%2FEAFuJ5pCLLM%2F1%2F0%2F1600w%2Fcanva-black-and-gold-simple-business-man-linkedin-profile-picture-BM_NPo97JwE.jpg&imgrefurl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.canva.com%2Fprofile-pictures%2Ftemplates%2Flinkedin%2F&docid=Afab7c3CvMXqHM&tbnid=z7mwhQpVEbFl2M&vet=12ahUKEwja0M-d2o-FAxWWWUEAHZCeB10QM3oECDgQAA..i&w=1600&h=1600&hcb=2&itg=1&ved=2ahUKEwja0M-d2o-FAxWWWUEAHZCeB10QM3oECDgQAA', 6, 'Certified Behavior Consultant Canine (CBCC-KA)', 'Behaviorist:\r\nPet behaviorists focus on understanding and modifying animal behavior. They often work with both dogs and cats but may also specialize in other animals.\r\nTheir expertise lies in identifying and addressing behavioral issues such as fear, aggression, compulsive behaviors, and phobias.\r\nBehaviorists typically employ positive reinforcement techniques and may collaborate with veterinarians to address underlying medical causes for behavioral problems.', 2),
(10017, 'preetham', 'Ealing', 'Training for free flight or outdoor enrichment', 'https://www.google.com/imgres?q=linkedin%20profile%20picture&imgurl=https%3A%2F%2Fmonteluke.com.au%2Fwp-content%2Fgallery%2Flinkedin-profile-pictures%2F1.jpg&imgrefurl=https%3A%2F%2Fmonteluke.com.au%2Fcorporate-portraits%2Flinkedin-profile-picture%2F&docid=2ri__y1dISRoPM&tbnid=l_5hZ00MbwTVkM&vet=12ahUKEwiR1bqw2o-FAxU8QkEAHSjDCuc4ChAzegQIbxAA..i&w=1200&h=1200&hcb=2&ved=2ahUKEwiR1bqw2o-FAxU8QkEAHSjDCuc4ChAzegQIbxAA', 8, 'Karen Pryor Academy Certified Training Partner (KPA-CTP)', 'Cat Trainer:\r\nWhile less common than dog trainers, cat trainers specialize in teaching cats various behaviors and commands, such as using a litter box, coming when called, or walking on a leash.\r\nThey understand feline behavior and use positive reinforcement techniques to train cats effectively.', 6),
(10018, 'pratham', 'West Ealing', 'Reptile training (e.g., handling, target training)\r\n', 'https://www.google.com/imgres?q=linkedin%20profile%20picture&imgurl=https%3A%2F%2Fimgv3.fotor.com%2Fimages%2Fgallery%2Fa-man-profile-picture-with-blue-and-green-background-made-by-LinkedIn-Profile-Picture-Maker.jpg&imgrefurl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fotor.com%2Ffeatures%2Flinkedin-profile-picture-maker%2F&docid=AOjFnqnDpE_J-M&tbnid=iDBMqlryYH7_FM&vet=12ahUKEwiR1bqw2o-FAxU8QkEAHSjDCuc4ChAzegQIVhAA..i&w=600&h=600&hcb=2&ved=2ahUKEwiR1bqw2o-FAxU8QkEAHSjDCuc4ChAzegQIVhAA', 5, 'Association of Professional Dog Trainers (APDT) Certification', 'Animal Trainer (General):\r\nAnimal trainers work with a variety of animals beyond just dogs and cats, including exotic pets, birds, horses, and even marine mammals like dolphins.\r\nTheir responsibilities may include teaching animals specific behaviors for performances, film, or television, as well as training for practical purposes like assistance animals or police dogs.\r\nAnimal trainers need a deep understanding of animal behavior and learning theory, along with patience and excellent communication skills.', 4),
(10019, 'srushti', 'North Brentford', 'Separation anxiety training.', 'https://www.google.com/imgres?q=linkedin%20profile%20picture&imgurl=https%3A%2F%2Fmonteluke.com.au%2Fwp-content%2Fgallery%2Flinkedin-profile-pictures%2Fcache%2F9.JPG-nggid03122-ngg0dyn-591x591-00f0w010c010r110f110r010t010.JPG&imgrefurl=https%3A%2F%2Fmonteluke.com.au%2Fcorporate-portraits%2Flinkedin-profile-picture%2F&docid=2ri__y1dISRoPM&tbnid=1qYhcvga4-ztIM&vet=12ahUKEwja0M-d2o-FAxWWWUEAHZCeB10QM3oECBgQAA..i&w=591&h=591&hcb=2&ved=2ahUKEwja0M-d2o-FAxWWWUEAHZCeB10QM3oECBgQAA', 9, 'International Association of Animal Behavior Consultants (IAABC) Certification:', 'Service Dog Trainer:\r\nService dog trainers specialize in training dogs to assist individuals with disabilities. They may train dogs for tasks such as guiding the blind, alerting deaf individuals to sounds, or providing support for mobility-impaired individuals.\r\nThese trainers must have extensive knowledge of obedience training as well as specific tasks related to the needs of the individuals they are serving.\r\nThey often work closely with clients to customize training programs tailored to their specific needs.', 9),
(10020, 'payola', 'Illford', 'Early socialization and habituation.', 'https://www.google.com/imgres?q=linkedin%20profile%20picture&imgurl=https%3A%2F%2Fi.pinimg.com%2F736x%2F55%2Fa5%2F89%2F55a589c4c118141188f1396ebada5e9b.jpg&imgrefurl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pinterest.com%2Fpin%2Fwork-it--226094843782026284%2F&docid=Jg9Kyx4ChUr2jM&tbnid=D_Tu5kD7TentAM&vet=12ahUKEwja0M-d2o-FAxWWWUEAHZCeB10QM3oECG8QAA..i&w=682&h=1024&hcb=2&ved=2ahUKEwja0M-d2o-FAxWWWUEAHZCeB10QM3oECG8QAA', 7, 'Certified Professional Bird Trainer (CPBT-KA)', 'Therapy Animal Trainer:\r\nTherapy animal trainers prepare animals, usually dogs, to provide emotional support and companionship to people in various settings such as hospitals, nursing homes, schools, and disaster areas.\r\nThey focus on teaching animals to remain calm, friendly, and well-behaved in different environments and around various types of people.\r\nTherapy animal trainers often work with volunteer handlers who take their trained animals to visit people in need of emotional support.', 7),
(10021, 'bhoomi', 'Central London', 'Behavior modification (e.g., aggression, fear, separation anxiety)\r\n\r\n', 'https://www.google.com/imgres?q=linkedin%20profile%20picture&imgurl=https%3A%2F%2Fwritestylesonline.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F01%2FThree-Things-To-Consider-When-Deciding-On-Your-LinkedIn-Profile-Picture-1024x1024.jpg&imgrefurl=https%3A%2F%2Fwritestylesonline.com%2Fthree-things-to-consider-when-deciding-on-your-linkedin-profile-picture%2F&docid=AD3ZI8D4s9irPM&tbnid=_cWTCa2OEpPQ0M&vet=12ahUKEwja0M-d2o-FAxWWWUEAHZCeB10QM3oECGYQAA..i&w=1024&h=1024&hcb=2&ved=2ahUKEwja0M-d2o-FAxWWWUEAHZCeB10QM3oECGYQAA', 8, 'Certified Feline Training and Behavior Specialist (CFTBS)', 'Falconry Trainer: Falconry trainers work with birds of prey, such as falcons, hawks, and eagles, training them for hunting or for educational demonstrations. They use traditional methods of training, including positive reinforcement and operant conditioning, to develop a strong bond between the bird and the falconer.', 6);

